The issue occurs because the second `System.out.print` starts with a carriage return `\r`, which immediately moves the cursor back to the start of the line and overwrites the text printed by the first `System.out.print`. Additionally, the variable `contador` is never incremented inside the loop.

To fix this, combine the counter and the progress bar into a single `System.out.print` call and increment `contador` after each song is processed.

```java
package umg.edu.gt.model;

import umg.edu.gt.data_structure.queue.manual.QueueLinked;

public class MediaPlayer {
	private QueueLinked<Song> MusicList = new QueueLinked<>();

	public MediaPlayer(QueueLinked<Song> MusicList)
	{
		this.MusicList = MusicList;
	}

	public void reproduce(QueueLinked<Song> MusicList) {
		int contador = 1;
		while (!MusicList.isEmpty()) {
			Song song = MusicList.peek();
			int duration = song.getDuration();
			System.out.println("Song #" + contador + " - Playing: " + song.getTitle());

			for (int i = 0; i <= duration; i++) {
				try { Thread.sleep(1000); } catch (Exception e) { Thread.currentThread().interrupt(); }

				int progress = (i * 20) / duration;
				String bar = "====================".substring(0, progress) + "                    ".substring(progress);
				// Combine both outputs into one to prevent overwriting
				System.out.print("\r[" + bar + "] " + i + "/" + duration + "s");
			}
			System.out.println("\nFinished: " + song.getTitle() + "\n");
			MusicList.dequeue();
			contador++; // Increment the counter for the next song
		}
	}
}
```

To allow the counter to persist across different lists, the `reproduce` method is modified to accept a starting value and return the final value.

1.  Update the `reproduce` method in `MediaPlayer.java` to take an `int startingCount` and return the updated `int` counter.
2.  In `Main.java`, store the result of the first call in a variable and pass it to the second call.
3.  Combine the song information in the output to ensure the carriage return `\r` does not overwrite the song index.

In `MediaPlayer.java`:

```java
package umg.edu.gt.model;

import umg.edu.gt.data_structure.queue.manual.QueueLinked;

public class MediaPlayer {
	private QueueLinked<Song> MusicList = new QueueLinked<>();

	public MediaPlayer(QueueLinked<Song> MusicList)
	{
		this.MusicList = MusicList;
	}

	public int reproduce(QueueLinked<Song> MusicList, int startingCount) {
		int contador = startingCount;
		while (!MusicList.isEmpty()) {
			Song song = MusicList.peek();
			int duration = song.getDuration();
			System.out.println("Song #" + contador + " - Playing: " + song.getTitle());

			for (int i = 0; i <= duration; i++) {
				try { Thread.sleep(1000); } catch (Exception e) { Thread.currentThread().interrupt(); }

				int progress = (i * 20) / duration;
				String bar = "====================".substring(0, progress) + "                    ".substring(progress);
				System.out.print("\r[" + bar + "] " + i + "/" + duration + "s");
			}
			System.out.println("\nFinished: " + song.getTitle() + "\n");
			MusicList.dequeue();
			contador++;
		}
		return contador;
	}
}
```

In `Main.java`:

```java
package umg.edu.gt.data_structure.queue.queueHandler;

import umg.edu.gt.data_structure.queue.manual.QueueLinked;
import umg.edu.gt.model.Song;
import umg.edu.gt.model.MediaPlayer;
import umg.edu.gt.model.PlaylistManageer;

class Main 
{
    public static void main( String[] args )
    {

    	Song song1 = new Song ("Glimpse of us","Joji",5,1);
    	Song song2 = new Song ("Mania Cardiaca","Enjambre",5,2);
    	Song song3 = new Song ("MELT","MASS OF FERMENTING DREGS",5,1);

    	QueueLinked<Song> HighPriority = new QueueLinked<>();
    	QueueLinked<Song> NormalPriority = new QueueLinked<>();

    	PlaylistManageer Priority = new PlaylistManageer(HighPriority,NormalPriority);

    	Priority.addSong(song1);
    	Priority.addSong(song2);
    	Priority.addSong(song3);

    	MediaPlayer playerHigh = new MediaPlayer(HighPriority);
    	MediaPlayer playerNormal = new MediaPlayer(NormalPriority);

    	int currentSongCount = 1;
    	// The counter is updated after the high priority list finishes
    	currentSongCount = playerHigh.reproduce(HighPriority, currentSongCount);
    	playerNormal.reproduce(NormalPriority, currentSongCount);
    }
}
```
